description.plain:
Terry Wallace (born March 23, 1994), better known as Tee Grizzley, is a platinum-selling hip hop recording artist from Detroit, Michigan.

Raised on Joy Road in West Detroit, Tee Grizzley was originally known as ASBH Tee of the Allstars BallHard crew. Years later, Grizzley burst back onto the hip hop scene with the release of his debut single, “First Day Out,” in 2016 after serving almost three years in prison for home invasion. The song quickly became a viral hit and led to Grizzley signing a deal with 300 Entertainment under the label Atlantic Records.

Tee then went on to release multiple singles, including the platinum-selling record “From the D to the A,” featuring Lil Yachty. In April 2017, Tee Grizzley released his debut commercial mixtape, My Moment, which hit #44 on the Billboard 200 chart even without a guest feature. In December of 2017, Tee followed up the success of My Moment with Bloodas, a collaborative mixtape with Chicago rapper Lil Durk.

In May of 2018, Grizzley released his first official album, Activated, which hit the top ten of the Billboard 200 list.

In November of 2018, Grizzley released Still My Moment. A much anticipated follow up to My Moment, the mixtape features the likes of Chance the Rapper, Quavo, Offset, and Lil Pump.

Laced with menacing beats and executive production from Timbaland, Grizzley released his 2nd studio album, Scriptures on the 7th of June in 2019. He released his third project, The Smartest, one year later in June of 2020.

description.plain:
After a nearly three-year stint behind bars, Detroit rapper Tee Grizzley has a lot of items to address during his first day out.

Grizzley’s hard-hitting and deeply personal bars propelled this song to viral fame, generating over three million views in just two weeks. Two months after releasing this song, he landed a deal with 300 Entertainment.

description.plain:
“From The D to the A” sees Tee Grizzley recruit Atlanta rapper Lil Yachty for a hard song about what they like spending money on, their ways with women, and their activity in the streets. The title is a nod to the artists' hometowns, with Tee Grizzley hailing from Detroit and Lil Yachty being from Atlanta.

The song marks the first collaboration between the two artists, produced by frequent Grizzley producer, Helluva Beats, who also produced Grizzley’s breakout hit “First Day Out”.

Grizzley first previewed the song on Twitter a week before its release saying:

To all the fans that’s ready for me and @lilyachty to light shit up Y'all gone love this We got y'all ⛵️🐻🔥🔥🔥

description.plain:
Tee Grizzley premieres his last preview for his debut mixtape “My Moment”, which was released on April 7th, 2017.  The song itself is a showoff of Grizzley’s gun talk and flow changes throughout the song combined with the producing talents of Helluva Beats, who also produced his breakthrough single “First Day Out”.

In the video to the song, he also receives a cosign from the stand-up comedian and actor Mike Epps.
